{"id":"gen-1769111399-DL3Mn9R4QDk22mspfh69","provider":"OpenAI","model":"openai/o4-mini-high","object":"chat.completion","created":1769111399,"choices":[{"logprobs":null,"finish_reason":"stop","native_finish_reason":"completed","index":0,"message":{"role":"assistant","content":"The factorial of a positive integer n is defined as  \nn! = n × (n–1) × (n–2) × … × 2 × 1\n\nFor n = 5:\n\n1. 5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1  \n2. Compute step by step:  \n   • 5 × 4 = 20  \n   • 20 × 3 = 60  \n   • 60 × 2 = 120  \n   • 120 × 1 = 120  \n\nTherefore, 5! = 120.","refusal":null,"reasoning":"**Calculating the factorial of 5**\n\nThe question asks for the factorial of 5 and to show the work behind it. So, I think it’s best to break it down step by step. \n\nThe calculation is:  \n- 5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1  \n- Moving through the multiplication: 5 × 4 = 20, 20 × 3 = 60, 60 × 2 = 120, and 120 × 1 = 120. \n\nTherefore, the factorial of 5 is 120. That's a clear answer!","reasoning_details":[{"format":"openai-responses-v1","index":0,"type":"reasoning.summary","summary":"**Calculating the factorial of 5**\n\nThe question asks for the factorial of 5 and to show the work behind it. So, I think it’s best to break it down step by step. \n\nThe calculation is:  \n- 5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1  \n- Moving through the multiplication: 5 × 4 = 20, 20 × 3 = 60, 60 × 2 = 120, and 120 × 1 = 120. \n\nTherefore, the factorial of 5 is 120. That's a clear answer!"},{"id":"rs_0f1e7e06c71bf6d70169727f681d4481959ed4a62be2f717f6","format":"openai-responses-v1","index":0,"type":"reasoning.encrypted","data":"gAAAAABpcn9tUz0UILsvOjklP1AgTCNZJLPiO1dJ7fCJExGd0TTINq0fKq34_6TGANBZ968n85JQVM_JPzk2dwMZZKMzfzJRQ5fjyXmC5hojvOmcILJBMTpYsfGOb3DTyujBv-I_jaCya_-H8VvdQsrnfwQpelSMfqn3z67TOsLdxMDmg6FmuFzQ153FNPMQ7htGQJYxdxJebCY0eIx7uUdmBAB18Ye6FEg5Fr1qckH6a2IXdGuqRFBY6CYxQg9BpQjV5HtPeirzA2Qnd-N3Am-jYFDVzSdzB2fTdhbLdSSjUe2_7hRGjpT2IfLPZ_AgObUhdbFj5dJwISOeXeEGQkacrg7M2TaF7lj7tqNCEulrbKXTQ-D5YP2MoJP2dr83C5E3NT1it8sc0tMuZie9zJca6kUTnzFAbsCtM